Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.45,0:00:12.49,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,It's been a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.62,0:00:16.18,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,Londark!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.28,0:01:54.00,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing here, Londark?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.29,0:01:56.64,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,Don't make that scary face.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.10,0:02:00.01,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,There's no need for us to fight now...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.45,0:02:03.01,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,As long as you do not interfere.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.37,0:02:07.52,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know what you're doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.77,0:02:09.71,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.71,0:02:13.52,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,I'm doing a job and getting paid,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.23,0:02:17.73,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,guiding and protecting this iron train.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.29,0:02:20.41,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,And what of the result?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.41,0:02:21.70,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,Result?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.70,0:02:25.46,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,There's nothing about that in my manual.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.91,0:02:27.65,Default - italics,L,0000,0000,0000,,Inferno Strike!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.83,0:02:33.09,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,Of course there isn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.09,0:02:38.59,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,I never received a manual for this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.63,0:02:44.60,Title,S,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1531,1)}Birthday Song
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.23,0:02:42.46,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Birthday Song.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.59,0:02:53.11,Default - flashback,C,0000,0000,0000,,You believe there's a possibility of war \Nwith People of the Land, Shiroe?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.63,0:02:57.15,Default - flashback,S,0000,0000,0000,,I think the Round Table should \Nconsider the possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.65,0:03:02.61,Default - italics,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,We're in a world where there's \Na possibility of war breaking out.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.61,0:03:07.16,Default - italics,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,That's what Shiroe was trying to say then.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.85,0:03:10.08,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,How will each individual
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.08,0:03:12.87,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,who lives in this world confront that possibility?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.87,0:03:15.11,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,That was his message.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.33,0:03:17.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Londark...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.60,0:03:21.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you trying to spread war and \Nchaos throughout the world?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.76,0:03:24.12,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.54,0:03:27.35,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,The ones who might be thinking of doing that
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.35,0:03:30.18,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,are the People of the Land \Nwho gave me this quest!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.53,0:03:33.10,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,And you're helping them!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.73,0:03:34.86,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,So,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.47,0:03:37.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,what of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.05,0:03:40.53,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,Many People of the Land will be lost!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.83,0:03:42.83,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,That's what they want.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.83,0:03:44.80,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,They fight because they want to.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.80,0:03:45.78,Default - italics,L,0000,0000,0000,,Frost—
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.09,0:03:54.75,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,We can stop it before it starts!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.23,0:03:58.24,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,I've never heard about a quest like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.50,0:04:03.15,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,You can't do anything if it isn't a quest, Londark?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.42,0:04:05.35,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up, hypocrite.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.35,0:04:10.41,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,I wasn't... I wasn't invited to this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.51,0:04:15.02,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,I wasn't invited to this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.98,0:04:18.81,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,I'm useless.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.36,0:04:24.03,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,Did you pick from a dialogue box that said, \N"Will you go to another world? Y/N"?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.71,0:04:26.53,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.14,0:04:30.41,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,I was forced to come here, and nobody asked me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.88,0:04:33.13,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,You were invited, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.13,0:04:36.04,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,That's why you're so relaxed!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.46,0:04:37.43,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.78,0:04:41.26,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,None of us were invited.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.58,0:04:44.86,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,This world tried to do something \Nto me that I didn't want,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.86,0:04:47.01,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,regardless of my feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.56,0:04:50.76,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,So I'm going to do what I want to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.37,0:04:53.53,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,Am I wrong,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.06,0:04:56.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,swashbuckler?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.21,0:05:02.15,HUD1,L,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(173,1)\an9\c&HFEF5D7&\fs20}Nyanta /Swashbuckler, Lv. 92
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.94,0:05:05.38,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.38,0:05:06.99,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,Are we done already?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.89,0:05:11.62,Default - italics,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,What Londark says is true.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.62,0:05:14.96,Default - italics,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,He was brought here with no say-so, \Nand he can't go back, even if he wants to.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.06,0:05:19.77,Default - italics,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,Adventurers are both victims and outsiders.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.77,0:05:24.42,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,It's natural for them to feel \Nanger at this unreasonable world.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.30,0:05:24.42,SignB,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7}Status: {\c&H4645B3&}Combat
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.30,0:05:24.42,SignC,,0000,0000,0000,,Stroganoff /Adventurer \N\N\NLycopin /Adventurer
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.30,0:05:24.42,SignD,,0000,0000,0000,,Smash /Adventurer
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.30,0:05:30.35,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,It's possible to eliminate Londark \Nand the other adventurers
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.35,0:05:33.18,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,with this problem by force.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.78,0:05:34.68,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.37,0:05:40.93,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,But what will that solve?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.00,0:05:44.49,Default - italics,L,0000,0000,0000,,Turbulence!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.48,0:05:48.57,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.08,0:05:52.54,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,If there's anything else I can do, tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.08,0:05:58.73,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,Are you saying I should just let \Nthis world screw with me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.66,0:06:11.14,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,Londark... That's true for everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.62,0:06:15.10,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,It's true for all children.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.33,0:06:24.70,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,People... At least, all children
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.37,0:06:29.32,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,are born into a world that seems \Nunreasonable and crazy to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.32,0:06:30.72,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.82,0:06:43.67,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,No one is asked at birth if they \Nagree to come into the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.24,0:06:48.67,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone is born that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.67,0:06:54.18,HUD1,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(238,1)\an9\c&HFEF5D7&\fs20}Nyanta /Swashbuckler, Lv. 92
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.19,0:06:54.18,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,In this world... In our old world... In any world!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.48,0:06:56.93,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,Is that all you can do?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.42,0:07:03.44,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,You can lecture me, but in the end, \Nyou can't get rid of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.27,0:07:06.91,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,There is no death here...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.91,0:07:10.20,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,So kill me if you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.20,0:07:12.20,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,End me, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.48,0:07:13.95,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,Swash—
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.54,0:07:22.46,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Is this what you wanted, Londark?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.60,0:07:32.48,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it wonderful being an adventurer?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.48,0:07:35.55,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,You can kill as much as you want, \Nand die as much as you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.72,0:07:37.77,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.22,0:07:40.52,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you kill him?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.52,0:07:43.51,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,I just shut him up for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.51,0:07:47.16,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Like he said, death isn't the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.84,0:07:50.76,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,It's like moving into the next room, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.12,0:07:54.28,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,To an adventurer, that's what death is.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.28,0:07:55.67,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's not!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.67,0:07:58.54,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,What makes you say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.54,0:08:00.30,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.30,0:08:04.52,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,I am General of the Punitive \NExpedition, Mizufa Trudy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.02,0:08:06.54,HUD1,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(381,1)\an9}Mizufa Trudy {\fs18}\NRace/ Human \NWarlord, Lv. 68 \NPlant Hwyaden
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.52,0:08:06.54,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the one in charge on the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.90,0:08:11.05,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,Are you the one who hired Londark?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.46,0:08:14.51,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,Is that how the People of the Land do things?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.87,0:08:18.86,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,You're still talking about that nonsense?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.86,0:08:21.44,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,People of the Land? Adventurers?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.44,0:08:23.33,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.77,0:08:26.67,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone who is born into this world
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.67,0:08:29.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,uses the cards they have to kill each other!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.53,0:08:32.59,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,The strong use their strength as their weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.59,0:08:35.53,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,The weak use their weakness as their weapon!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.52,0:08:40.58,Default - italics,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,She's strong!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.05,0:08:43.54,Default - italics,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,She's so strong, it's hard to believe \Nshe's a Person of the Land!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.54,0:08:48.21,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,You can't die, but you're going to talk \Nto me about conquest and ruling?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.62,0:08:50.76,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you want war?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.82,0:09:04.20,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to burn my life down
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.20,0:09:06.10,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,with the alcohol called "war."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.44,0:09:08.75,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Dance, undead!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.11,0:09:12.53,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,"Undead"?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.53,0:09:15.57,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,It's the perfect name for you \Npeople who can't die, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.94,0:09:17.30,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.50,0:09:20.16,Default - italics,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,Viper's Rush!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.95,0:09:25.27,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Amazing...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.27,0:09:27.02,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Wonderful!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.02,0:09:29.08,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Almost enough to make me fall in love with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.45,0:09:32.34,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,But your blade lacks the desire to kill!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.32,0:09:35.61,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,Is that what you're proud of?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.61,0:09:37.43,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,Your desire to kill?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.82,0:09:40.18,Default - italics,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,Early Thrust!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.38,0:10:00.19,HUD1,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7\fad(466,1)}Kazuhiko \N{\fs18}Race/ Human \NAssassin, Lv. 97 \NPlant Hwyaden
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.87,0:09:58.51,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,Kazuhiko...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.33,0:10:09.04,Default - italics,D,0000,0000,0000,,Astral Hypno.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.19,0:10:17.98,Default - italics,N,0000,0000,0000,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.43,0:10:22.01,Default - italics,N,0000,0000,0000,,I was just planning to interfere a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.03,0:10:24.85,Green HUD,N,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(218,1)\an7\fs20}Dariella /Chronicler
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.35,0:10:25.72,Default - italics,N,0000,0000,0000,,I thought it would be easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.16,0:10:29.44,Default - italics,N,0000,0000,0000,,No, I actually managed to fit in, didn't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.22,0:10:36.36,Default - italics,N,0000,0000,0000,,Just the slightest sign that I cared for \Nthem, and they all trusted me...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.84,0:10:41.25,Default - italics,N,0000,0000,0000,,Only Shiro is special.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.25,0:10:43.03,Default - italics,N,0000,0000,0000,,They aren't.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.39,0:10:46.41,Default - italics,N,0000,0000,0000,,They're only members of the same guild.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.41,0:10:48.04,Default - italics,N,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.35,0:10:49.45,Default - italics,N,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.45,0:10:52.04,Default - flashback,T,0000,0000,0000,,You wouldn't look weird without that smile.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.69,0:10:56.05,Default - flashback,D,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.35,0:10:58.05,Default - flashback,T,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.08,0:11:03.55,Default - flashback,T,0000,0000,0000,,Because that way, you wouldn't \Nlook like you were lying.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.60,0:11:06.39,Default - flashback,T,0000,0000,0000,,You'd look better that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.04,0:11:11.96,Default - italics,D,0000,0000,0000,,That little child had a blade hidden in his heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.49,0:11:14.32,Default - italics,D,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.69,0:11:17.41,Default - italics,D,0000,0000,0000,,Shiro's teachings are that boy's blade.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.27,0:11:20.98,Default - italics,D,0000,0000,0000,,Shiro really is special.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.98,0:11:22.32,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Lady Nureha!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.38,0:11:26.17,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Lady Nureha, this is a war zone.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.59,0:11:28.47,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Would you please leave?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.01,0:11:32.33,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Why is this happening to this town?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.06,0:11:34.47,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Mizufa's orders?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.47,0:11:35.39,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.39,0:11:36.34,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.89,0:11:41.33,Default - italics,D,0000,0000,0000,,I agreed to Mizufa's orders because \NI thought they didn't matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.00,0:11:44.20,Default - italics,D,0000,0000,0000,,I came here because I was asked to.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.70,0:11:46.61,Default - italics,D,0000,0000,0000,,But in this town...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.11,0:11:55.84,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Annihilate as many of the wyverns and \Nnightshade servants as you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.18,0:11:58.74,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Is that all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.26,0:12:01.36,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,It is the order of the Western Councilor.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.36,0:12:02.27,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.72,0:12:12.04,Default - italics,D,0000,0000,0000,,Shiro, I'm going to give them a little help.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.04,0:12:16.13,Default - italics,D,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't for long, but they treated me \Nas a fellow traveling companion...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.10,0:12:19.45,Default - italics,D,0000,0000,0000,,Will you notice?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.45,0:12:21.56,Default - italics,D,0000,0000,0000,,Will you think me a bother?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.98,0:12:24.32,Default - italics,D,0000,0000,0000,,Or will you think I did well?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.81,0:12:28.96,Default - italics,D,0000,0000,0000,,This is just a whim of mine, not a gift to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.68,0:12:31.48,Default - italics,D,0000,0000,0000,,So hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.48,0:12:35.48,Default - italics,D,0000,0000,0000,,I can't wait to hear your voice...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.21,0:12:49.08,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,It's been a while, Chief.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.61,0:12:51.27,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Since the Tea Party, maybe?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.88,0:12:54.52,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,Move, Kazuhiko.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.37,0:12:57.33,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,I need to correct something.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.87,0:12:58.86,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.48,0:13:00.96,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,I can't do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.92,0:13:04.97,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you involved in this?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.67,0:13:07.58,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,It's something I have to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.38,0:13:14.26,Default - italics,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,Kazuhiko is trying to change Plant \NHwyaden for the better from inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.26,0:13:15.94,Default - italics,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,That's what Shiroe said.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.78,0:13:22.54,Default - italics,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,But he's lost his own goodness now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.54,0:13:24.90,Default - italics,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,That's how he looks to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.90,0:13:27.70,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,You're so slow!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.09,0:13:33.04,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Operation Red Night has already begun!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.53,0:13:38.72,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,That's why you adventurers \Ncan't be this world's heroes!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.72,0:13:40.11,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Now sleep!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.11,0:13:42.37,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,You won't die, anyway!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.86,0:13:50.97,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Mizufa...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.97,0:13:53.35,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,You're strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.35,0:13:56.54,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, you're very strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.54,0:13:57.94,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,But it's no good.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.94,0:14:01.48,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Your kindness is going to get you killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.99,0:14:06.70,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Your desire to save the People of the \NLand is going to get them killed!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.93,0:14:13.83,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Now, what will you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.90,0:14:21.42,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Mizufa, it's over.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.42,0:14:23.40,Default,Ni,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be stupid...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.77,0:14:26.19,Default,Ni,0000,0000,0000,,You're just an observer!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.19,0:14:28.49,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,It's an order from Nureha.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.49,0:14:32.79,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Just now, the highest-ranking order \Nhas been given to Plant Hwyaden.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.57,0:14:34.84,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,We're withdrawing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.84,0:14:36.43,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,The mission is canceled.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.84,0:14:45.19,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,Kazuhiko, what is Plant Hwyaden thinking?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.51,0:14:46.76,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,What are you—
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.76,0:14:48.07,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Enough talk!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.23,0:14:53.17,Default - italics,K,0000,0000,0000,,This is still better.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.07,0:15:07.86,Default - italics,K,0000,0000,0000,,The Chief won't have to kill \Nany People of the Land.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.97,0:15:13.93,Default - italics,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,Is it because you used to be my friend, Kazuhiko?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.54,0:15:18.96,Default - italics,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think you're showing me \Na fragment of friendship?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.43,0:15:26.94,Default - italics,R,0000,0000,0000,,Orb of Lava!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.68,0:15:38.45,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.92,0:15:40.46,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Those kids...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.36,0:15:49.92,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,There's nothing I can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.42,0:16:03.44,Default,Ro,0000,0000,0000,,Little brothers and sisters!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.02,0:16:07.44,Default,Ro,0000,0000,0000,,Your sister isn't going to abandon you!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.55,0:16:11.84,Default,Ro,0000,0000,0000,,The first friends I made in this world are angry
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.84,0:16:14.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,at this place that only creates sadness.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.46,0:16:17.06,Default,Ro,0000,0000,0000,,A fallen country's abandoned princess,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.06,0:16:19.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,once unable to make friends with anyone,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.16,0:16:21.21,Default,Ro,0000,0000,0000,,is crying within me!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.57,0:16:26.84,Default,Ro,0000,0000,0000,,You, whose contract was once \Nbroken, walk with me!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.46,0:16:30.55,Default - italics,Ro,0000,0000,0000,,Sword Princess Al Quenje!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.88,0:17:03.21,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.72,0:17:10.76,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,I can't do anything, but I'll sing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.22,0:17:12.57,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,I'm watching.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.03,0:17:16.35,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,I'll tell you I'm watching you all.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.28,0:17:19.97,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,To tell you that...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.66,0:17:22.91,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,Songs are small things.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.91,0:17:25.26,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,There isn't much they can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.79,0:17:28.63,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how much you sing that \Nyou want to change the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.63,0:17:30.93,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,no matter how great an artist you are,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.93,0:17:35.34,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,music alone can't bring peace to the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.99,0:17:38.66,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,But... But I'll sing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.06,0:17:41.29,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,I know you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.29,0:17:43.56,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,I know how you feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.91,0:17:47.75,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,Songs are prayers that are actually heard.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.40,0:17:51.59,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,I understand how you feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.59,0:17:53.90,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,When I sing, I feel the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.31,0:17:55.51,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,Don't give in.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.51,0:17:56.55,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,Hang in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.07,0:17:59.58,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,That's what everyone was trying to tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.90,0:18:03.34,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,I can't say that I'll become an artist.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.79,0:18:08.40,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,But I can promise I'll love music my whole life!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.71,0:18:12.89,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,Rudy longed to be an adventurer.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.89,0:18:15.36,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,It didn't matter whether he could be or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.36,0:18:18.86,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,He just wanted to fight what he saw as unreasonable.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.79,0:18:23.74,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't need to worry about whether I had talent.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.24,0:18:26.91,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,Rudy brought me close.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.91,0:18:30.17,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,He gave me my songs.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.01,0:18:34.82,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Isuzu!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.82,0:18:36.26,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Serara!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.26,0:18:37.51,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.51,0:18:41.99,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,I searched all the buildings west \Nof here with Wolfie's nose.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.45,0:18:45.82,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,All the People of the Land have evacuated.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.82,0:18:47.88,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Get back, mister!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.54,0:18:50.34,HUD1,T,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(769,1)\an9}Party Chat \N{\fs20}Tohya \NMinori \NIsuzu \NRundel Haus Code \NSerara \NRoe 2
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.88,0:18:48.75,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Tohya...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.75,0:18:49.89,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.89,0:18:51.91,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You're still going to get in my way?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.91,0:18:54.87,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,This battle belongs to the Odyssey Knights!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.15,0:18:53.59,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,He's still fighting.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.11,0:18:56.36,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, Tohya hasn't lost yet, either!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.36,0:18:58.21,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,He's near the river.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.21,0:18:59.19,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,He's close!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.19,0:19:01.95,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Don't mess up until I get there, Tohya!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.95,0:19:03.86,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I, Rundel Haus Code,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.37,0:19:07.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,will help you!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.62,0:19:09.22,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,I won't step down!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.54,0:19:16.30,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not going to give up on you guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.10,0:19:19.88,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,What does a kid like you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.23,0:19:22.18,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't stop,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.18,0:19:25.06,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I'll rip you apart with my Onslaught!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.06,0:19:26.58,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Then do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.06,0:19:29.49,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm not leaving!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.49,0:19:30.39,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Tohya!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.07,0:19:35.65,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,This is the place where we die.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.65,0:19:38.21,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Don't block our path to hell!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.86,0:20:02.95,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Tohya...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.42,0:20:04.47,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Give me a break!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.50,0:20:07.93,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,The place where you die?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.68,0:20:11.55,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,A path to hell?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.27,0:20:13.94,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Isuzu?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.16,0:20:16.20,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Rudy...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.72,0:20:22.24,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,I want to fill this world with the \Nsound of a forty-third song!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.67,0:20:26.20,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,I want to play the song I made for \Nthe first time in this world!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.24,0:20:31.21,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,Because...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.74,0:20:33.26,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,This world...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.71,0:20:40.67,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,This world I've walked through with my friends...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.66,0:20:43.80,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,It isn't...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.35,0:20:45.56,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,It isn't...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.49,0:20:50.72,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,the path to hell!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.11,0:20:58.76,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,The sea wind, the asphalt...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.76,0:21:01.97,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,Once we're over the hill,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.97,0:21:05.20,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,we can see the next town.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.20,0:21:09.49,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,Our journey is just beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.44,0:21:17.77,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,Plucking the strings on my little lute,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.77,0:21:20.97,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,I'll open up the window
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.97,0:21:25.01,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,and begin again today.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.60,0:21:33.58,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you can't hear this song,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.58,0:21:39.82,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,even if you're locked inside this tiny world,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.82,0:21:43.06,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,it's okay
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.06,0:21:46.25,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,because I'm here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.25,0:21:54.09,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,I'll overwrite the yesterday \Nthat hurt your heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.09,0:22:01.93,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,I won't forget the shining rainbow I spread,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.93,0:22:07.52,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,and my hopes will become musical notes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.52,0:22:14.62,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,I won't forget the shining promise I made with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.62,0:22:22.10,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,Even my cowardly lute is different today.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.54,0:24:08.21,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,The journey is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.21,0:24:10.30,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,What were they able to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.30,0:24:12.22,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,Were they able to save anyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.22,0:24:13.99,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,Minori and the others still feel glum.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.58,0:24:18.19,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,Roe 2 entrusts them with a letter for Shiroe.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.73,0:24:22.80,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,Meanwhile, a new threat approaches Akihabara.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.27,0:24:30.94,Title,Title,0000,0000,0000,,The Skylarks Take Flight
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.41,0:24:25.84,Default,Next time,0000,0000,0000,,Next time: The Skylarks Take Flight.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.38,0:24:28.28,Default,Next time,0000,0000,0000,,I have friends to run with me.
